  <thing id="io5CRuinsto" name="Ruinstone" description="Once a day, a villain holding this palm-sized red crystal can use a bonus action to undo one thing they have done. In combat, this typiclaly allows for the reversal of one action or the rerolling of a failed save.\n\nEvery time the ruinstone is used, someone the wielder knows is disintegrated and erased from reality. Roll a d20: on a 5-20, it&apos;s an ally of the villain. On a 1-4, it&apos;s one of the player characters. \n\nIf a creature has bound its soul to the ruinstone, the artifact explodes on use. The creature whose soul is bound disappears from reality and can only be brought back via a {i}wish{/i} spell or similar magical effect." compset="Wondrous">
